{
  "stem": "717.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So the factories were going until the Germans wanted to dissolve the ghetto, or maybe it was because the-- the Allies and the Russians came closer and closer and they wanted to go away further into Germany.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So around July, I think, they started dissolving the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we were hiding, my mother, myself, and I think another relative.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I think it was the mother of my aunt, the one that gave away the little girl.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I don't know how come she was staying with us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The two women hid in bed, and I think I hid under the bed or something.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They passed us by.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And then we-- we went, we were hiding on the cemetery for a few days.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Didn't even come back to sleep.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We thought we'll be able to get away with it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But how long can you be outside, no food, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So when we came back, they came for us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I remember the soldiers coming up the stairs in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] Street, we lived, with machine guns.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Not with the usual brutality, nothing extraordinary, nothing that scared us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We were used to it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And they took-- we were prepared to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We had a rucksack, you know, a backpack with-- I think there was a limit on how much you could carry, so we took some clothes with us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Didn't need it anyway.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They told us we're going to go, we're going to be resettled to a different camp, work camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And the elderly people are going to be separate, the children are going to separate and taken care of.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "The old people are going to be taken care of.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
